AWS Practical: Launch Ubuntu EC2 and Configure Apache Web Server

Question

Launch an Ubuntu EC2 instance named Lab_Q1_Apache and configure the security group to allow:

- SSH (Port 22)
- HTTP (Port 80)

Install Apache2 Web Server and create a webpage at:

/var/www/html/index.html

The webpage should display your PRN number.

Verify that the website is accessible using the EC2 instance's Public IP Address.

---



Step 1: Launch Ubuntu EC2 Instance

Navigate to:

AWS Console → EC2 → Launch Instance

Configuration:

Name: Lab_Q1_Apache
AMI: Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS
Instance Type: t2.micro

Create Key Pair:

apache-key

Download:

apache-key.pem

---

Step 2: Configure Security Group

Create Security Group:

Apache-SG

Inbound Rules:

Type| Port| Source
SSH| 22| My IP
HTTP| 80| Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0)

Outbound Rules:

Type| Destination
All Traffic| 0.0.0.0/0

Launch Instance.

---

Step 3: Obtain Public IP

Navigate:

EC2 → Instances → Lab_Q1_Apache

Copy:

Public IPv4 Address

Example:

13.233.xxx.xxx

---

Step 4: Configure PEM File Permissions (Windows)

Open PowerShell as Administrator.

Run:

icacls "D:\Users\ABHISHEK KUMAR\Downloads\apache-key.pem" /inheritance:r

icacls "D:\Users\ABHISHEK KUMAR\Downloads\apache-key.pem" /grant:r "Abhishek:(R)"

icacls "D:\Users\ABHISHEK KUMAR\Downloads\apache-key.pem" /remove "Authenticated Users" "Users" "Everyone"

---

Step 5: Connect to Ubuntu EC2

Open PowerShell.

Command:

ssh -i "D:\Users\ABHISHEK KUMAR\Downloads\apache-key.pem" ubuntu@<PUBLIC-IP>

Example:

ssh -i "D:\Users\ABHISHEK KUMAR\Downloads\apache-key.pem" ubuntu@13.233.xxx.xxx

Accept host key:

yes

Verify login:

hostname

Expected:

ip-172-31-x-x

---

Step 6: Update Ubuntu Packages

sudo apt update

---

Step 7: Install Apache2

sudo apt install apache2 -y

Verify:

sudo systemctl status apache2

Expected:

active (running)

---

Step 8: Enable Apache Service

sudo systemctl enable apache2

Start Apache:

sudo systemctl start apache2

---

Step 9: Create Web Page

Open index.html:

sudo nano /var/www/html/index.html

Add:

<html>
<head>
<title>AWS Apache Practical</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>PRN: YOUR_PRN_NUMBER</h1>
</body>
</html>

Example:

<html>
<head>
<title>AWS Apache Practical</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>PRN: 240340120001</h1>
</body>
</html>

Save:

CTRL + O
ENTER
CTRL + X

---

Alternative Method (Single Command)

echo "<h1>PRN: 240340120001</h1>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

---

Step 10: Verify File

cat /var/www/html/index.html

Expected:

<h1>PRN: 240340120001</h1>

---

Step 11: Test Website from Browser

Open Chrome.

Visit:

http://<PUBLIC-IP>

Example:

http://13.233.xxx.xxx

Expected Output:

PRN: 240340120001

---

Verification

Apache Service

sudo systemctl status apache2

Result:

active (running)

---

Website Access

http://<PUBLIC-IP>

Displays:

PRN: YOUR_PRN_NUMBER

